	details = <
		["nb"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::nb]>
			purpose = <"*To record details about a single condition, problem or diagnosis that may be responsible for the clinical presentation, examination findings and/or test results until a single, working diagnosis is determined. (en)">
			use = <"*To record details about a single condition, problem or diagnosis that may be responsible for the clinical presentation, examination findings and/or test results, until a working, provisional or preliminary diagnosis is determined.

This archetype has been strategically designed to ensure that each informal, unconfirmed or possible diagnosis is recorded using a unique model that is temporary and only appropriate in the earliest phases of the diagnostic process. A diagnosis that is intended for persistence will be recorded using the EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis archetype.

In a clinical system, it would be expected that each differential diagnosis would be recorded using a separate instance of this archetype. As further evidence is gathered from test results, investigations or referrals, the status of each differential diagnoses will be updated until each one is excluded or a single working or preliminary diagnosis is identified. It is anticipated that this archetype may be used within the context of an encounter, or a Problem list. (en)">
			keywords = <"*differential (en)", "*diagnosis (en)">
			misuse = <"*Not to be used to record detailed information about a persistent problem or formal diagnosis - use the EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis for this purpose. (en)">
		>
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"To record details about a single condition, problem or diagnosis that may be responsible for the clinical presentation, examination findings and/or test results until a single, working diagnosis is determined.">
			use = <"To record details about a single condition, problem or diagnosis that may be responsible for the clinical presentation, examination findings and/or test results, until a working, provisional or preliminary diagnosis is determined.

This archetype has been strategically designed to ensure that each informal, unconfirmed or possible diagnosis is recorded using a unique model that is temporary and only appropriate in the earliest phases of the diagnostic process. A diagnosis that is intended for persistence will be recorded using the EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis archetype.

In a clinical system, it would be expected that each differential diagnosis would be recorded using a separate instance of this archetype. As further evidence is gathered from test results, investigations or referrals, the status of each differential diagnoses will be updated until each one is excluded or a single working or preliminary diagnosis is identified. It is anticipated that this archetype may be used within the context of an encounter, or a Problem list.">
